Favorite: LNIB AA Piston kit with upgraded complete Voodoo Innovations low mass BCG. I put this on a Short Barrel Rifle and shot a 20 round box of Gemtech 300BLK 187 Subs with it and then traded the upper minus the piston kit to a friend. It comes with the complete AA kit plus the full BCG and a pistol length drive rod, the ID of the gas block is .750"    This design of this piston system is just incredible, especially when shot suppressed. It has 5 different gas settings for numerous applications (ie, subsonic) and is unique in that it can fit under most handguards that use a standard barrel nut, instead of having the block poking up in front of the handguard and disrupting the profile. It also is legitimately self-cleaning, and designed to shoot around 10,000 rounds before requiring to be cleaned. These kits are for a mid-length setup, but pistol, carbine and rifle length drive rods can be purchased separately from Adams Arms to fit whatever length is required.    These run between $360-$380 + s/h + tax depending on where you buy them and that's without the VDI Lifecoat complete bolt that I have. The complete Lifecoat VDI bolts are between $55-$80 before shipping and or taxes.     Here is the description from AA's website:     This system will work with .223/5.56 x 45 mm NATO and 300BLK    Kit includes:    Patented One-Piece Low Mass Bolt Carrier  XLP Multi-Adjustable Low Profile Gas Block  Gas Plug  Bushing Installation Rod  Bolt Spring  Drive Rod with Bushing and Spring  Installation DVD  The Adams Arms Piston System:    A short stroke free floating piston system.  Is Self-Cleaning.  Carbon and gases are expelled forward, away from operator.  Corrosive resistant coating processes.  Harmonics are not transferred into the barrel.  Adjustable gas settings for various applications.  Doesn't vent directly to atmospheric pressure; this eliminates flash signature and super sonic crack which is optimal for night vision and suppresses fire.    I am willing to ships a well, add $25 for shipping within the lower 48. I also have more pictures if needed as well as the original foam box and packaging.
